article:
Colchester United Football Club is an English football club based in Colchester,
Essex. Formed in 1937, Colchester joined the Southern Football League and were
elected to the Football League in 1950. Their promotion to came as a result of
the excellent FA Cup run of 1948. The club stayed in the lower reaches of the
league for their early years, and in 1962 the club finished runners-up in
Division 4 and had been between the third and fourth tiers of the League for
many years. 1990 saw them relegated to the Conference, although two years later
they won that League and the FA Trophy to complete the non-league "Double".
Colchester were promoted to the Championship for the first time in their history
in 2006, spending two years in the second tier, before being relegated back to
League One, where they currently play.

Micky Cook holds the record for total appearances with 700 in all
competitions. He also holds the record for most league appearances
with 613 between 1969 and 1984. Martyn King holds the record for most
league goals (131) between 1959 and 1965. Tony Adcock holds the record for most
goals in all competitions with 149 goals.
